Chelsea have released their squad that will tackle Valencia in Tuesday’s Champions League group stage clash at Stamford Bridge. The Blues have already confirmed that Antonio Rudiger, Emerson Palmieri and Ruben Loftus-Cheek are injured. Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard, has also disclosed in his pre-match press conference on Monday that Mason Mount, Tammy Abraham and Fikayo Tomori are excited to take on Valencia. Chelsea head to the game following a 5-2 victory over Wolves during Premier League at Molineux last weekend. Chelsea’s provisional squad: Arrizabalaga, Azpilicueta, Christensen, Zouma, Jorginho, Mount, Giroud, Pedro, Pulisic, Caballero, Alonso, Tomori, Barkley, Kovacic, Willian, Abraham, Batshuayi. Meanwhile, Valencia have already released a 20-man squad to face Chelsea. Valencia’s squad against Chelsea: Domenech, Cillessen, Rivero, Thierry, Costa, Paulista, Diakhaby, Gaya, Wass, Garay, Kondogbia, Guedes, Parejo, Cheryshev, Kang, Coquelin, Ferran, Gameiro, Rodrigo, Gomez The kick-off time for the match is 8pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.